HEADWORD: Dotard
<hw>Do"tard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<er>Dote</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>One whose mind is impaired by age; one in
second childhood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sickly <qex>dotard</qex> wants a wife.</q> <rj><qau>
Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dotardly</ent>⟦br⟧
